<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1445,2010]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1589,1613]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is a patronym in honor of Dr. M. E. Galiano, who made great contributions in taxonomic studies of jumping spiders from the Neotropical region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1445,2010]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1661,1686]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[446,673,1661,1685]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Ilargus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moronatigus">
<emphasis box="[446,673,1661,1685]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Ilargus moronatigus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in color and markings (
<figureCitation box="[939,1069,1661,1685]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1894,1917]" captionTargetBox="[174,1435,426,1864]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,411,1873]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Ilargus galianoae sp. nov. 60 male holotype, dorsal view; 61 female paratype, dorsal view; 62 male left palp, ventral view; 63 male left palp, retrolateral view; 64 female left chelicera, back view; 65 epigynum, ventral view; 66 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 60 – 61, 0.5 mm; 62 – 66, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209894/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Figs 
<number box="[996,1069,1661,1685]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="60.5" valueMax="61.0" valueMin="60.0">60–61</number>
</figureCitation>
), but can be distinguished by the large epigynal window, the presence of the wave-shaped ridges in the window (
<figureCitation box="[1115,1205,1697,1721]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1894,1917]" captionTargetBox="[174,1435,426,1864]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,411,1873]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Ilargus galianoae sp. nov. 60 male holotype, dorsal view; 61 female paratype, dorsal view; 62 male left palp, ventral view; 63 male left palp, retrolateral view; 64 female left chelicera, back view; 65 epigynum, ventral view; 66 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 60 – 61, 0.5 mm; 62 – 66, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209894/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 
<number box="[1174,1205,1697,1721]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="65.0">65</number>
</figureCitation>
), and the long and convoluted copulatory duct (
<figureCitation box="[475,560,1733,1757]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1894,1917]" captionTargetBox="[174,1435,426,1864]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,411,1873]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Ilargus galianoae sp. nov. 60 male holotype, dorsal view; 61 female paratype, dorsal view; 62 male left palp, ventral view; 63 male left palp, retrolateral view; 64 female left chelicera, back view; 65 epigynum, ventral view; 66 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 60 – 61, 0.5 mm; 62 – 66, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209894/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 
<number box="[528,560,1733,1757]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="66.0">66</number>
</figureCitation>
). Also differs from other 
<taxonomicName box="[849,929,1733,1757]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Ilargus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[849,929,1733,1757]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Ilargus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the shape of the male palpal bulb (
<figureCitation box="[159,244,1769,1793]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1894,1917]" captionTargetBox="[174,1435,426,1864]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,411,1873]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Ilargus galianoae sp. nov. 60 male holotype, dorsal view; 61 female paratype, dorsal view; 62 male left palp, ventral view; 63 male left palp, retrolateral view; 64 female left chelicera, back view; 65 epigynum, ventral view; 66 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 60 – 61, 0.5 mm; 62 – 66, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209894/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,244,1769,1793]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="62.0">62</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1445,2010]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1805,1830]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[356,414,1805,1829]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[432,534,1805,1829]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">holotype</typeStatus>
, UBC-SEM AR00150). Carapace length 
<number box="[1018,1056,1805,1829]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1.5">1.5</number>
; abdomen length 
<number box="[1267,1305,1805,1829]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="1.7">1.7</number>
. Chelicera: yellow brown. Palp (
<figureCitation box="[395,531,1841,1865]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1894,1917]" captionTargetBox="[174,1435,426,1864]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,411,1873]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Ilargus galianoae sp. nov. 60 male holotype, dorsal view; 61 female paratype, dorsal view; 62 male left palp, ventral view; 63 male left palp, retrolateral view; 64 female left chelicera, back view; 65 epigynum, ventral view; 66 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 60 – 61, 0.5 mm; 62 – 66, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209894/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Figs 
<number box="[455,531,1841,1865]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="62.5" valueMax="63.0" valueMin="62.0">62–63</number>
</figureCitation>
): yellowish to brown. Embolus long and coiled for about a circle; retrolateral sperm duct occupying about two thirds of bulb width; retrolateral tibial apophysis finger-like; ventral tibial bump absent. Measurements of legs: I 
<number box="[523,560,1913,1937]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="3.1">3.1</number>
, II 
<number box="[601,639,1913,1937]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2.6">2.6</number>
, III 3.0, IV 
<number box="[778,816,1913,1937]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="3.5">3.5</number>
. Color in alcohol (
<figureCitation box="[1032,1118,1913,1937]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1894,1917]" captionTargetBox="[174,1435,426,1864]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,411,1873]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Ilargus galianoae sp. nov. 60 male holotype, dorsal view; 61 female paratype, dorsal view; 62 male left palp, ventral view; 63 male left palp, retrolateral view; 64 female left chelicera, back view; 65 epigynum, ventral view; 66 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 60 – 61, 0.5 mm; 62 – 66, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209894/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 
<number box="[1086,1118,1913,1937]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="60.0">60</number>
</figureCitation>
): carapace gray brown with indistinctive yellowish markings, eye area dark brown, behind eye area with a narrow sandy yellow stripe; abdomen brown sandy in color, with brownish markings and speckles; legs bisque, with gray brown annuli.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,151,356]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis box="[199,283,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Female</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[303,404,151,175]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">paratype</typeStatus>
, UBC-SEM AR00151). Carapace length 
<number box="[895,933,151,175]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1.6">1.6</number>
; abdomen length 2.0. Chelicera (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1424,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1894,1917]" captionTargetBox="[174,1435,426,1864]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,411,1873]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Ilargus galianoae sp. nov. 60 male holotype, dorsal view; 61 female paratype, dorsal view; 62 male left palp, ventral view; 63 male left palp, retrolateral view; 64 female left chelicera, back view; 65 epigynum, ventral view; 66 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 60 – 61, 0.5 mm; 62 – 66, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209894/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Fig. 
<number box="[1391,1424,151,175]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="64.0">64</number>
</figureCitation>
): yellow brown. Measurements of legs: I 
<number box="[627,664,188,212]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.8">2.8</number>
, II 
<number box="[712,750,188,212]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="2.6">2.6</number>
, III 
<number box="[807,844,188,212]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.1">3.1</number>
, IV 
<number box="[903,942,188,212]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="3.8">3.8</number>
. Epigynum (
<figureCitation box="[1094,1184,188,212]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1894,1917]" captionTargetBox="[174,1435,426,1864]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,411,1873]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Ilargus galianoae sp. nov. 60 male holotype, dorsal view; 61 female paratype, dorsal view; 62 male left palp, ventral view; 63 male left palp, retrolateral view; 64 female left chelicera, back view; 65 epigynum, ventral view; 66 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 60 – 61, 0.5 mm; 62 – 66, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209894/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Fig. 
<number box="[1152,1184,188,212]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="65.0">65</number>
</figureCitation>
): window large, with transverse wave-shaped ridges in the window; median septum relatively narrow; opening to copulatory duct at anterior margin of window. Vulva (
<figureCitation box="[555,641,260,284]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1894,1917]" captionTargetBox="[174,1435,426,1864]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,411,1873]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Ilargus galianoae sp. nov. 60 male holotype, dorsal view; 61 female paratype, dorsal view; 62 male left palp, ventral view; 63 male left palp, retrolateral view; 64 female left chelicera, back view; 65 epigynum, ventral view; 66 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 60 – 61, 0.5 mm; 62 – 66, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209894/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Fig. 
<number box="[609,641,260,284]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="66.0">66</number>
</figureCitation>
): copulatory duct long and convoluted, with accessory gland near the beginning; spermatheca almost kidney-shaped. Color in alcohol (
<figureCitation box="[901,988,295,319]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="16.[151,264,1894,1917]" captionTargetBox="[174,1435,426,1864]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,411,1873]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Ilargus galianoae sp. nov. 60 male holotype, dorsal view; 61 female paratype, dorsal view; 62 male left palp, ventral view; 63 male left palp, retrolateral view; 64 female left chelicera, back view; 65 epigynum, ventral view; 66 cleared epigynum, dorsal view. Scale bars: 60 – 61, 0.5 mm; 62 – 66, 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/209894/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Fig. 
<number box="[956,988,295,319]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="61.0">61</number>
</figureCitation>
): similar to that of male, but abdomen dark brown with brown sandy markings and speckles.
</paragraph>
